    Use Zeckendorf (Fibonacci) base digit-DP. Represent numbers < N in the
    Fibonacci-base (no consecutive ones). Count total set bits (ones) across all
    valid representations using DP over positions with a tight flag.

    Key ideas: combinatorics on binary strings without consecutive ones,
    precompute Fibonacci numbers or combinatorial counts for lengths, digit-DP
    to aggregate counts of ones for numbers < N. Expected time O(log N),
    space O(log N).

Answer: ...
